        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "For it was the king's commandment concerning them",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Artaxerxes, it appears, had assigned a certain stipend from the royal revenue for the support of such Levites as were singers, and this stipend had to be paid to them day by day. It is suggested as the grounds for this special favour - ",
        "children": []
